# **1. Overview ****&**** Objectives**

This document is a Claude Code implementation plan for the FORGE marketplace MVP — specifically the Seller Onboarding and AI Sales Page Generation module. It is written as a structured build brief: each section maps directly to a Claude Code prompt sequence, tool selection decision, or integration task.

FORGE is a no-code / low-code first build. The goal is a working, sellable MVP using the fastest available tooling — not a custom-engineered system. Every tool decision in this spec reflects that constraint.

|  | *Scope of this spec: Seller registration → product URL submission → AI crawl and extraction → auto-generated sales page draft → seller review and publish. This is the critical path that makes the marketplace viable.* |
| --- | --- |

## **1.1 Success Criteria for MVP**

The seller onboarding module is complete when all of the following are true:

- A seller can register, create a profile, and submit a product URL in under 10 minutes

- The platform crawls the submitted URL and extracts: product name, description, feature list, use-cases, and screenshots

- Claude API generates a structured sales page draft from extracted data automatically

- Seller can review, edit, and publish the sales page without writing a single line of copy

- Published page is live, publicly accessible, and includes pricing configuration

- Entire flow functions without custom backend code — using no-code/low-code tooling

# **2. Recommended Tech Stack**

Stack decisions are optimised for three constraints: speed to MVP, non-technical operator (Clifton), and Claude Code as the primary implementation agent. Every tool below can be configured via Claude Code prompts without deep developer expertise.

| **Layer** | **Tool** | **Tier** | **Rationale** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Frontend / UI | Webflow | Starter ($14/mo) | Visual builder, CMS-ready, no-code. Claude Code can generate embed scripts. |
| Database / Auth | Supabase | Free → Pro | Postgres + Auth + Storage in one. Claude Code has strong Supabase pattern support. |
| Automation / Logic | Make (Integromat) | Core ($9/mo) | No-code workflow engine. Handles crawl trigger → Claude API → page creation chain. |
| AI Generation | Claude API (Sonnet) | Pay-as-you-go | Sales page generation, copy writing, feature extraction from crawled content. |
| Web Scraping | Firecrawl | Hobby ($16/mo) | Purpose-built for LLM-ready content extraction from URLs. Make-compatible. |
| Payments | Stripe | Pay-as-you-go | Industry standard. Supabase + Stripe integration well-documented for Claude Code. |
| File Storage | Supabase Storage | Included | Screenshot uploads, seller assets. Supabase bucket with public URL generation. |
| Email | Resend | Free → $20/mo | Transactional email. Simple API, Make-compatible, excellent deliverability. |

|  | *Claude Code prompt tip: When starting each module, open Claude Code and begin with: **'**I am building a no-code marketplace MVP called FORGE. My stack is Webflow (frontend), Supabase (database/auth), Make (automation), and Claude API (AI generation). I am non-technical and need step-by-step implementation. Begin with [module name].**'* |
| --- | --- |

# **3. System Architecture**

## **3.1 Data Flow — Seller Onboarding to Published Page**

The end-to-end flow is a linear pipeline with five stages. Each stage maps to a specific tool and a Claude Code implementation task.

| **Step** | **Stage** | **Tool** | **Output** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| 1 | Seller Registration | Webflow + Supabase Auth | Seller account created, profile stored in Supabase sellers table |
| 2 | Product URL Submission | Webflow Form → Make | Form submission triggers Make scenario with product URL payload |
| 3 | Content Extraction | Make → Firecrawl API | Structured JSON: title, description, features, screenshots, meta |
| 4 | AI Page Generation | Make → Claude API | Full sales page copy: headline, subhead, features, CTA, pricing block |
| 5 | Draft Review & Publish | Webflow CMS + Supabase | Seller edits draft in Webflow editor, publishes — page goes live |

## **3.2 Supabase Schema — Core Tables**

The following tables form the MVP database. Claude Code can generate the full SQL migration script from this specification.

