| Create a Supabase SQL migration for a marketplace called FORGE. Generate these tables with appropriate column types and RLS policies: sellers (id, user_id, display_name, bio, avatar_url, tool_tags[],          stripe_account_id, created_at, verified boolean) products (id, seller_id, title, tagline, description, features jsonb,            use_cases jsonb, screenshots text[], demo_url, video_url,            price_licensed numeric, price_exclusive numeric,            status [draft│live│archived], created_at) sales_pages (id, product_id, headline, subheadline, body_copy text,              cta_text, meta_title, meta_description, published_at) Enable Row Level Security. Sellers can only read/write their own records. Products are publicly readable when status = live. |
