# **4. Seller Onboarding — Build Sequence**

This section provides the exact implementation sequence for Claude Code. Each phase is an independent Claude Code session. Complete each phase fully before starting the next.

| **1** | **Supabase Setup — Auth + Database** Configure Supabase project, enable email auth, run schema migration, configure RLS policies, generate API keys for Make integration. |
| --- | --- |

| **2** | **Webflow Seller Registration Flow** Build registration page in Webflow. Integrate Supabase Auth via Webflow embed. Create seller profile form. Connect form submission to Supabase sellers table via Make. |
| --- | --- |

| **3** | **Product Submission Form** Build product submission page in Webflow. Fields: product URL, product name (auto-populated), category, pricing, demo link. Form triggers Make on submit. |
| --- | --- |

| **4** | **Make Automation — URL Submission to Draft** Build Make scenario: receive form data → call Firecrawl API with URL → parse response → call Claude API with extracted content → write generated copy to Supabase sales_pages table → send confirmation email via Resend. |
| --- | --- |

| **5** | **Seller Draft Review Interface** Build Webflow CMS page that reads draft sales page from Supabase. Seller can edit inline fields (headline, body, pricing). Save triggers Supabase update. Publish button sets status to live. |
| --- | --- |

| **6** | **Public Product Listing Page** Build Webflow CMS template for live product pages. Pulls from Supabase via Make or direct API. Includes screenshot gallery, video embed slot, pricing, seller profile panel, CTA buttons. |
| --- | --- |

# **5. Firecrawl Integration — Content Extraction**

## **5.1 What Firecrawl Does**

Firecrawl crawls the seller's submitted product URL and returns clean, structured, LLM-ready markdown content — stripping navigation, ads, and boilerplate. This is the raw material for Claude API to generate the sales page.

## **5.2 Make Scenario — Firecrawl Module**

**CLAUDE CODE PROMPT — BUILD MAKE SCENARIO STEP**

| I am building a Make (Integromat) scenario for FORGE marketplace. Step 3 of my scenario receives a product URL from a Webflow form submission. Build the Firecrawl API module configuration for Make: - Endpoint: POST https://api.firecrawl.dev/v1/scrape - Headers: Authorization: Bearer {{FIRECRAWL_API_KEY}} - Body: { url: {{form.product_url}}, formats: ['markdown','screenshot'],           onlyMainContent: true } Map the response to these Make variables: - scraped_markdown: response.data.markdown - screenshot_url: response.data.screenshot - page_title: response.data.metadata.title - page_description: response.data.metadata.description Show me the exact JSON module config I paste into Make. |
| --- |

## **5.3 Extraction Quality — Fallback Handling**

Firecrawl works well for most modern web apps but may return thin content for single-page apps rendered client-side. Build these fallbacks into the Make scenario:

- If scraped_markdown length < 500 characters: trigger email to seller requesting manual description input

- If screenshot_url is null: flag product as screenshot-pending; seller uploads manually via dashboard

- If page_title is null: use seller-entered product name from form as fallback

# **6. Claude API — Sales Page Generation**

## **6.1 The Generation Prompt**

This is the core prompt sent to Claude API inside the Make scenario. It transforms Firecrawl's raw markdown into structured, buyer-facing sales copy. This prompt should be treated as a primary product asset — iterate it based on real seller output quality.

**MASTER SYSTEM PROMPT — SALES PAGE GENERATOR**

| You are a senior SaaS copywriter for FORGE, a marketplace where AI builders sell apps and tools to small businesses. Your job is to write compelling, clear, and honest sales page copy from raw product content. TONE: Direct, benefit-led, jargon-free. Written for an SME owner who is not technical. Avoid hype. Focus on what the buyer gains, not how it works. OUTPUT FORMAT — return valid JSON only, no preamble: {   "headline": "8-12 word headline — benefit-led, not feature-led",   "subheadline": "20-30 word elaboration of the core benefit",   "problem_statement": "2-3 sentences: the pain this product solves",   "features": [{ "title": "", "description": "" }],  // 4-6 items   "use_cases": ["Who uses this and for what — 3-5 scenarios"],   "social_proof_placeholder": "What kind of testimonial to request",   "cta_primary": "Button text — action verb + benefit",   "cta_secondary": "Secondary action text",   "meta_title": "SEO title under 60 chars",   "meta_description": "SEO description under 155 chars" } |
| --- |

**USER MESSAGE TEMPLATE (POPULATED BY MAKE)**

| Product Name: {{page_title}} Product URL: {{form.product_url}} Category: {{form.category}} Seller Description: {{form.seller_description}} Crawled Content: {{scraped_markdown}} Generate the sales page JSON now. |
| --- |

## **6.2 Claude Code Prompt — Make API Module**

**CLAUDE CODE PROMPT — WIRE CLAUDE API IN MAKE**

| I am building step 4 of a Make scenario for FORGE marketplace. I have these variables from the previous step:   - scraped_markdown, page_title, screenshot_url, form.category,     form.product_url, form.seller_description Configure an HTTP module in Make to call the Anthropic Claude API: - URL: https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages - Method: POST - Headers:     x-api-key: {{ANTHROPIC_API_KEY}}     anthropic-version: 2023-06-01     content-type: application/json - Body: use the system prompt and user message template I provide - Model: claude-sonnet-4-5-20251001 - Max tokens: 2000 Parse response.content[0].text as JSON. Map each field to Make variables for the next step. Show me the exact HTTP module configuration. |
| --- |

## **6.3 Storing Generated Output**

**CLAUDE CODE PROMPT — WRITE TO SUPABASE**

| In my Make scenario, step 5 receives these variables from Claude API:   headline, subheadline, problem_statement, features (JSON array),   use_cases (JSON array), cta_primary, cta_secondary,   meta_title, meta_description And from earlier steps: product_id (from Supabase insert in step 2), screenshot_url, seller_id Configure a Supabase HTTP module in Make to: 1. INSERT into products table: title, seller_id, status='draft',    screenshots=[screenshot_url], created_at=now() 2. INSERT into sales_pages table: product_id, headline, subheadline,    body_copy (stringify the full JSON), meta_title, meta_description Show me both Supabase API calls with exact request bodies. |
